{
  "text": "Vertigo is known to be poorly prognostic, but commonly encountered in sudden SNHL patients [CITATION_1] . Vertigo is not a disease, but rather a symptom; our focus was on BPPV, which commonly causes peripheral vertigo accompanied by sudden SNHL. BPPV could cause by migration of otoloith into semicircular canals, it might be a factor that means severe labyrinth damage [CITATION_2] . Thus, sudden SNHL patients with BPPV may exhibit more severe labyrinth damage associated with poorer recovery then we could suppose that these patients would show poor recovery.",
  "correct_citation": {
